{
  "stem": "17720.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 126.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the synagogue of Sofia was one of the biggest and more beautiful in the Balkans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the, the life of the Jewish people was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] pretty much connected with this synagogue.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They-- inside of the synagogue, they, they used to have school, a very big school, starting from the preschool-- very, very well organized.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is where, actually, I started my very early learning, studying, studying of the Hebrew language also.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, later on, when I went to Israel, was absolutely forgotten everything there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But never less, the life there was pretty, pretty rich.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] the Jewish families were visiting each other was where I, I remember how often my mother used to be visited of my aunts, my uncles, as well as other relatives.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so many times, she would prepare [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] her visits for these relatives also.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, she used to dress me a little bit neater, a little prettier.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I used to be prepared to sing some song or play something on my little xylophone.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or I had also one mouth harmonica.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had also one little this musical instrument, what is like vertical flutes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They call in Hebrew [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Here is--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Recorder-- yeah, one recorder, to which I was improvising some of the songs that I have learned, some of which were based in the music of the greatest masters, like famous songs of operas of Mozart, some songs of Schubert, of course, in children translation, child translation.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember how this used-- not only how it used to make her happy, but how this used to also astonish and make a very strong impression, impressions on the relatives and cousins.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
